The issue we are trying to solve is not only for lists and maps. I think you have to handle the union scenarios for pretty much each case here.
For example, for streams also it fails atm.
type Foo record {
    string id;
};

type Bar record {
    int id;
};


public function main() { 

    Foo[] fooList = [{id: "1234"}, {id: "5678"}];

    stream<Foo> fooStream = fooList.toStream();

    stream<Foo>|stream<Bar> fooBarStream = fooStream;

    record {|Foo|Bar value;|}|error? res = fooBarStream.next(); 
}

