timeline.bodyText:
I think we can generalize this and findTypeParamInUnionForMap.
    private void findTypeParamInUnion(DiagnosticPos pos, BType expType, BUnionType actualType,
                                      SymbolEnv env, HashSet<BType> resolvedTypes, FindTypeParamResult result) {
        LinkedHashSet<BType> memTypes = new LinkedHashSet<>();
        for (BType type : actualType.getMemberTypes()) {
            switch (type.tag) {
                case TypeTags.ARRAY:
                    memTypes.add(((BArrayType) type).eType);
                    break;
                case TypeTags.MAP:
                    memTypes.add(((BMapType) type).constraint);
                    break;
            }
        }
        BUnionType unionType = BUnionType.create(null, memTypes);
        findTypeParam(pos, expType, unionType, env, resolvedTypes, result);
    }
To this we can pass as expType the array element type or map constraint type.
e.g.,
findTypeParamInUnion(pos, ((BArrayType) expType).eType, (BUnionType) actualType, env, resolvedTypes, 
                     result);
I think this will be the cleaner approach when we're adding checks for the rest of the cases in findTypeParam too.

